      <style xml:id="basic" tts:textAlign="center" />
    </styling>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:03.120" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors. For this base camp,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:03.120" end="00:00:06.000" tts:direction="ltr">we're going to dive into the world of
<br />design,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:06.000" end="00:00:09.260" tts:direction="ltr">one of my favorite aspects of data
<br />visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:09.260" end="00:00:11.360" tts:direction="ltr">Our guiding question is,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:11.360" end="00:00:16.100" tts:direction="ltr">can you apply design principles for
<br />effective data communication?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:16.100" end="00:00:20.280" tts:direction="ltr">I hope you are going to be able to answer
<br />yes after this base camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:20.280" end="00:00:22.800" tts:direction="ltr">Let's talk about what we see.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:22.800" end="00:00:26.040" tts:direction="ltr">It's all about what we see and how we
<br />internalize that.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.040" end="00:00:27.940" tts:direction="ltr">Remember at the beginning of the course,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:27.940" end="00:00:31.280" tts:direction="ltr">I talked about these pre attentive
<br />attributes.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:31.280" end="00:00:36.460" tts:direction="ltr">These are attributes that we notice
<br />without using conscious effort to do so.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:36.460" end="00:00:38.540" tts:direction="ltr">And so is your audience.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:38.540" end="00:00:41.780" tts:direction="ltr">I might have an amazing insight that I
<br />have spent</p>
        <p begin="00:00:41.780" end="00:00:45.440" tts:direction="ltr">a lot of time gathering, colting
<br />calculating,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:45.440" end="00:00:49.940" tts:direction="ltr">and then I present it to my audience and
<br />it's buried within a sea of</p>
        <p begin="00:00:49.940" end="00:00:54.860" tts:direction="ltr">colors or in something that's distracting
<br />like some bold text.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:54.860" end="00:00:58.120" tts:direction="ltr">Suddenly, my insight is lost and I've
<br />given</p>
        <p begin="00:00:58.120" end="00:01:02.200" tts:direction="ltr">my audience a harder job to understand
<br />that and to find that.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:02.200" end="00:01:05.640" tts:direction="ltr">Those pre attentive attributes are
<br />certainly present and</p>
        <p begin="00:01:05.640" end="00:01:09.320" tts:direction="ltr">design can really help guide your audience
<br />to that insight.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:09.320" end="00:01:11.200" tts:direction="ltr">Now I'm going to use an adage from</p>
        <p begin="00:01:11.200" end="00:01:14.680" tts:direction="ltr">our architect friends where form follows
<br />function.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:14.680" end="00:01:17.960" tts:direction="ltr">The function part is the actual data.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:17.960" end="00:01:20.480" tts:direction="ltr">That is the hero of our story,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:20.480" end="00:01:23.160" tts:direction="ltr">that is the star, and we cannot lose sight
<br />of that.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:23.160" end="00:01:25.120" tts:direction="ltr">Remember, we have a clear purpose,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:25.120" end="00:01:27.400" tts:direction="ltr">we have our audience, we have credible
<br />data,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:27.400" end="00:01:29.400" tts:direction="ltr">and we're using the right chart kind.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:29.400" end="00:01:31.965" tts:direction="ltr">Now we're going to layer on this design.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:31.965" end="00:01:35.810" tts:direction="ltr">Remember, function is what drives form,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:35.810" end="00:01:41.570" tts:direction="ltr">and form are these design principles that
<br />we're going to add to your toolbox.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:41.570" end="00:01:44.070" tts:direction="ltr">They should answer these questions.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:44.070" end="00:01:47.890" tts:direction="ltr">What insight is the visualization trying
<br />to share?</p>
        <p begin="00:01:47.890" end="00:01:51.630" tts:direction="ltr">How long does it take to identify the
<br />insight?</p>
        <p begin="00:01:51.630" end="00:01:55.070" tts:direction="ltr">Finally, what design elements of the Vz
<br />are most</p>
        <p begin="00:01:55.070" end="00:01:58.610" tts:direction="ltr">or least effective at communicating this
<br />insight.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:58.610" end="00:02:01.550" tts:direction="ltr">Here are some additional questions that
<br />after you</p>
        <p begin="00:02:01.550" end="00:02:04.590" tts:direction="ltr">are done with your design chart or
<br />dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:04.590" end="00:02:07.530" tts:direction="ltr">you should step back and really ask
<br />yourself,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:07.530" end="00:02:11.050" tts:direction="ltr">is it answering these questions?</p>
        <p begin="00:02:12.760" end="00:02:17.600" tts:direction="ltr">Last year, I had a chance to go to
<br />Copenhagen, Denmark.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:17.600" end="00:02:21.500" tts:direction="ltr">It was an amazing experience and I learned
<br />a ton.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:21.500" end="00:02:24.120" tts:direction="ltr">One of the things that I love doing
<br />whenever I</p>
        <p begin="00:02:24.120" end="00:02:27.080" tts:direction="ltr">get to a new country is to ride the public
<br />transit.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:27.080" end="00:02:28.780" tts:direction="ltr">Copenhagen is no different,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:28.780" end="00:02:32.000" tts:direction="ltr">it has an amazing system full of trust.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:32.000" end="00:02:33.900" tts:direction="ltr">But as you can imagine,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:33.900" end="00:02:35.640" tts:direction="ltr">as someone new to the city,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:35.640" end="00:02:38.660" tts:direction="ltr">looking at this map was very confusing.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:38.660" end="00:02:41.620" tts:direction="ltr">Now, it was a general map to a general
<br />audience.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:41.620" end="00:02:44.180" tts:direction="ltr">It didn't give me an exact purpose of
<br />where I</p>
        <p begin="00:02:44.180" end="00:02:47.280" tts:direction="ltr">could find my hotel or landmarks I was
<br />looking at,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:47.280" end="00:02:51.495" tts:direction="ltr">and it was just overwhelming for me to
<br />orient myself.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:51.495" end="00:02:53.990" tts:direction="ltr">Luckily, they had used some good design
<br />principles</p>
        <p begin="00:02:53.990" end="00:02:56.030" tts:direction="ltr">and I was able to interpret it,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:56.030" end="00:02:57.890" tts:direction="ltr">but it took a long time.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:57.890" end="00:03:01.570" tts:direction="ltr">I imagine there will come a day when I'll
<br />have some app where</p>
        <p begin="00:03:01.570" end="00:03:05.670" tts:direction="ltr">I'll be able to see the route highlighted
<br />and the other routes grade out.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:05.670" end="00:03:08.010" tts:direction="ltr">But in this case, it was just a static map</p>
        <p begin="00:03:08.010" end="00:03:10.750" tts:direction="ltr">that I had to navigate and really use.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:10.750" end="00:03:14.290" tts:direction="ltr">That friction, that frustration that</p>
        <p begin="00:03:14.290" end="00:03:18.090" tts:direction="ltr">I had is something that you're trying to
<br />avoid with your audience.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:18.090" end="00:03:22.890" tts:direction="ltr">Instead, you're going to help them see the
<br />narrative and the story to</p>
        <p begin="00:03:22.890" end="00:03:24.950" tts:direction="ltr">get to the inside or action that you are</p>
        <p begin="00:03:24.950" end="00:03:28.300" tts:direction="ltr">proposing that comes through intentional
<br />design.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:28.300" end="00:03:32.410" tts:direction="ltr">So our job as a data analyst is to use
<br />those visual cues</p>
        <p begin="00:03:32.410" end="00:03:37.040" tts:direction="ltr">to uncover insights and guide our audience
<br />to action.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:37.040" end="00:03:39.870" tts:direction="ltr">We're going to cover three design
<br />principles.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:39.870" end="00:03:41.570" tts:direction="ltr">Now this is not exhaustive.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:41.570" end="00:03:44.070" tts:direction="ltr">There are many more design principles out
<br />there,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:44.070" end="00:03:50.670" tts:direction="ltr">but I want you to really use these three
<br />as a starting point for data 3,400.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:50.670" end="00:03:54.430" tts:direction="ltr">We're going to talk about layout,
<br />contrast, and Gestalt.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:54.430" end="00:03:58.490" tts:direction="ltr">The first thing I want you to notice for
<br />this is that there is</p>
        <p begin="00:03:58.490" end="00:04:02.690" tts:direction="ltr">an opportunity for you to do some analog
<br />note taking if you so choose.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:02.690" end="00:04:06.350" tts:direction="ltr">Now I've provided a PDF file and you can
<br />download that if</p>
        <p begin="00:04:06.350" end="00:04:10.030" tts:direction="ltr">you've got two different colored pencils
<br />or markers,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:10.030" end="00:04:13.980" tts:direction="ltr">then you're welcome to grab those as well
<br />and follow along.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:13.980" end="00:04:19.410" tts:direction="ltr">As I'll help you through this note taking
<br />experience.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:19.410" end="00:04:22.350" tts:direction="ltr">Now, I do this because I know that when we
<br />learn,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:22.350" end="00:04:26.010" tts:direction="ltr">it's important to use as many senses as
<br />possible.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:26.010" end="00:04:28.630" tts:direction="ltr">You're using sight, you're using sound.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:28.630" end="00:04:31.190" tts:direction="ltr">Now if you can write, then you might be
<br />able to</p>
        <p begin="00:04:31.190" end="00:04:33.610" tts:direction="ltr">internalize some of these concepts a
<br />little bit deeper.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:33.610" end="00:04:37.250" tts:direction="ltr">I invite you to print it off and to follow
<br />along.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:37.290" end="00:04:39.530" tts:direction="ltr">Now to our layout,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:39.530" end="00:04:41.770" tts:direction="ltr">we're going to cover three items in the
<br />layout,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:41.770" end="00:04:45.215" tts:direction="ltr">headings, space, and then layout.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:45.215" end="00:04:47.420" tts:direction="ltr">First is headings.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:47.420" end="00:04:49.660" tts:direction="ltr">Now, we will talk about the importance of</p>
        <p begin="00:04:49.660" end="00:04:52.180" tts:direction="ltr">takeaway titles in our story base camp,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:52.180" end="00:04:55.000" tts:direction="ltr">but I want to use this as a layout
<br />principle.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:55.000" end="00:04:58.660" tts:direction="ltr">We know that headings are very important.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:58.660" end="00:05:01.480" tts:direction="ltr">Now, I have a chart here. It is something
<br />that maybe</p>
        <p begin="00:05:01.480" end="00:05:05.060" tts:direction="ltr">an Excel chart would default to. It's
<br />pretty basic.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:05.060" end="00:05:08.720" tts:direction="ltr">It is a telling versus a showing chart.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:08.720" end="00:05:12.220" tts:direction="ltr">It says, average retail product price per
<br />year.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:12.220" end="00:05:14.760" tts:direction="ltr">Now let me spend more time</p>
        <p begin="00:05:14.760" end="00:05:21.165" tts:direction="ltr">interpreting product ABC D and R. This is
<br />what I do not want to see.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:21.165" end="00:05:25.710" tts:direction="ltr">You should never just have the default
<br />title when you're presenting.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:25.710" end="00:05:29.430" tts:direction="ltr">Now, when you're analyzing and doing some
<br />internal work, that's different.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:29.430" end="00:05:32.510" tts:direction="ltr">We're talking about your time to present.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:32.510" end="00:05:34.730" tts:direction="ltr">Really thinking about that heading is</p>
        <p begin="00:05:34.730" end="00:05:38.170" tts:direction="ltr">an important principle that I want to
<br />convey to you right now.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:38.170" end="00:05:42.070" tts:direction="ltr">Instead, you can go beyond those defaults
<br />and you</p>
        <p begin="00:05:42.070" end="00:05:46.535" tts:direction="ltr">can begin to show like this one that I've
<br />got here.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:46.535" end="00:05:50.380" tts:direction="ltr">To be competitive, we recommend
<br />introducing our products below</p>
        <p begin="00:05:50.380" end="00:05:55.540" tts:direction="ltr">the $240 average price point in the one 50
<br />to 200 range.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:55.540" end="00:05:58.600" tts:direction="ltr">Now, a general principle in marketing is
<br />to</p>
        <p begin="00:05:58.600" end="00:06:02.220" tts:direction="ltr">always use 5-7 words for a billboard.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:02.220" end="00:06:04.220" tts:direction="ltr">As you're driving down 15,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:04.220" end="00:06:06.680" tts:direction="ltr">you're going 80 miles per hour</p>
        <p begin="00:06:06.680" end="00:06:08.600" tts:direction="ltr">and you only really have</p>
        <p begin="00:06:08.600" end="00:06:11.420" tts:direction="ltr">a chance to read something that's five to
<br />seven words.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:11.420" end="00:06:14.050" tts:direction="ltr">That's the headline principle.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:14.050" end="00:06:17.410" tts:direction="ltr">We can break that here in our
<br />visualizations and have more</p>
        <p begin="00:06:17.410" end="00:06:21.570" tts:direction="ltr">because our audience is going to read so
<br />that they can interpret.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:21.570" end="00:06:23.490" tts:direction="ltr">Putting those two things together,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:23.490" end="00:06:27.330" tts:direction="ltr">will really help get your audience further
<br />down to that insight.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:27.330" end="00:06:28.910" tts:direction="ltr">But these are a lot of words,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:28.910" end="00:06:31.990" tts:direction="ltr">and there's always a start and there's
<br />always iteration.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:31.990" end="00:06:34.370" tts:direction="ltr">If you have a concept or an idea,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:34.370" end="00:06:40.050" tts:direction="ltr">plug it into GPT and see if they can
<br />reform it to maybe seven to ten words,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:40.050" end="00:06:42.550" tts:direction="ltr">maybe five words, and then that's a chance
<br />for you to</p>
        <p begin="00:06:42.550" end="00:06:45.470" tts:direction="ltr">get a little bit tighter on the language
<br />that you're using.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:45.470" end="00:06:49.260" tts:direction="ltr">In this case, Here is a new header where
<br />it says,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:49.260" end="00:06:55.540" tts:direction="ltr">competitive target price point 150-200 and
<br />below the 240 average.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:55.540" end="00:06:57.900" tts:direction="ltr">This is a chance to really again,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:57.900" end="00:06:59.860" tts:direction="ltr">take my audience a little further.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:59.860" end="00:07:02.900" tts:direction="ltr">Now, I haven't applied any other design
<br />principles, but you can see,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:02.900" end="00:07:09.860" tts:direction="ltr">I can already understand my context of my
<br />target price point 150-200.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:09.860" end="00:07:12.360" tts:direction="ltr">That's the recommendation I'm giving you
<br />as my analyst.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:12.360" end="00:07:15.780" tts:direction="ltr">We want to make sure that we're below the
<br />240 average.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:15.780" end="00:07:19.820" tts:direction="ltr">So Here's another example of a very much</p>
        <p begin="00:07:19.820" end="00:07:23.700" tts:direction="ltr">of a tell title Acme, full time employees.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:23.700" end="00:07:25.460" tts:direction="ltr">Well, yeah, that's what it is.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:25.460" end="00:07:30.960" tts:direction="ltr">But my role as a data analyst is to give
<br />you some insight to take you further.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:30.960" end="00:07:33.920" tts:direction="ltr">I'm not just going to tell I'm going to
<br />show.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:33.920" end="00:07:39.380" tts:direction="ltr">I can modify this header by using this
<br />headline. Please approve.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:39.380" end="00:07:41.080" tts:direction="ltr">Notice I'm using a verb,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:41.080" end="00:07:44.460" tts:direction="ltr">the hire of two FTEs that stands for</p>
        <p begin="00:07:44.460" end="00:07:48.580" tts:direction="ltr">a full time employee to backfill those who
<br />quit in the past year.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:48.580" end="00:07:52.320" tts:direction="ltr">Now I've got this lovely line chart over
<br />time,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:52.320" end="00:07:56.820" tts:direction="ltr">and I'm seeing that there was a spike in
<br />July, there were employees,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:56.820" end="00:08:00.680" tts:direction="ltr">we took a big hit, we climbed up and then
<br />we took another hit,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:00.680" end="00:08:03.960" tts:direction="ltr">and there's an opportunity to hire more
<br />individuals,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:03.960" end="00:08:07.600" tts:direction="ltr">and that's really the ask and I'm proving
<br />that with this data.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:07.600" end="00:08:10.100" tts:direction="ltr">Those two together is going to be a lot
<br />more of</p>
        <p begin="00:08:10.100" end="00:08:14.365" tts:direction="ltr">a compelling argument to get the resources
<br />that you would need.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:14.365" end="00:08:16.630" tts:direction="ltr">If you've got that printout,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:16.630" end="00:08:20.550" tts:direction="ltr">you can go ahead and write this takeaway
<br />title,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:20.550" end="00:08:25.450" tts:direction="ltr">please approve the two hires of two full
<br />time employees.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:25.450" end="00:08:27.850" tts:direction="ltr">You might even create another little dot.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:27.850" end="00:08:30.610" tts:direction="ltr">Maybe the dot goes up or something because
<br />you've now hired two.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:30.610" end="00:08:34.300" tts:direction="ltr">All right? Let's talk about space.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:34.300" end="00:08:39.400" tts:direction="ltr">This is an area of design that is often
<br />neglected.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:39.400" end="00:08:43.980" tts:direction="ltr">We love to just pile everything on to our
<br />pages and</p>
        <p begin="00:08:43.980" end="00:08:46.020" tts:direction="ltr">our reports so that we can</p>
        <p begin="00:08:46.020" end="00:08:49.220" tts:direction="ltr">maybe demonstrate the knowledge that we've
<br />been able to gather.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:49.220" end="00:08:52.980" tts:direction="ltr">Instead, I want you to think about how you
<br />can use space to</p>
